# An if/else chain with two live arms and one diverging (exit) arm,
# inside a quote used as an `iff` branch. The diverging arm must
# contribute nothing to the quote's inferred signature. Previously it
# leaked a `( -- <bottom>)` arm, making the quote overloaded so `iff`
# (which needs a plain quote) rejected it. This program runs correctly.
true
(
    true if
        'a'
    else* false *if
        'b'
    else
        1 exit
    end
)
('c')
iff
wl
